{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3411049,"name":"Umar Ali","username":"Ironman_87","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/i/e56c9b/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-07-25T02:30:45.345Z","cooked":"<p>Hello! Our team is encountering a problem with the “Command” class. We want some of the commands in the class to run parallel to each other, however, when we tried using the .parallel() method, it just ends up running the commands sequentially. Does anyone know a fix to this?<br>
<div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/c/2/c25b143b76d9907f3d4fad3d8033b6daadd8b935.jpeg" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/c25b143b76d9907f3d4fad3d8033b6daadd8b935" title="dsjafldj"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/c/2/c25b143b76d9907f3d4fad3d8033b6daadd8b935.jpeg" alt="dsjafldj" data-base62-sha1="rJlLrp9gLWzHkccXOaxAfsMxfw1" width="690" height="479" data-dominant-color="76756F"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">dsjafldj</span><span class="informations">932×648 65.9 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2024-07-25T02:30:45.345Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":10,"reads":141,"readers_count":140,"score":78.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":469111,"topic_slug":"command-groups-help","display_username":"Umar Ali","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":67318,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/command-groups-help/469111/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3411092,"name":"Gavin Matthews","username":"bovlb","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png","created_at":"2024-07-25T06:26:47.698Z","cooked":"<p>I suspect your problem is that you’re using <code>runOnce</code> to call long-running methods. WPILIB multitasking is cooperative and relies on your command methods being quick. If your methods don’t return until they’re done, then they will effectively run sequentially.</p>
<p>Consider splitting your command into a <code>run()</code> part and adding a termination condition using <code>until()</code>.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public Command getAutonomousCommandShoot(int ms, int charge) {
    return Commands.run(() -&gt; autonomousShootExecute(ms, charge))
        .until(() -&gt; autonomousShootIsFinished());
</code></pre>
<p>Also, it’s much easier to help you with programming problems if you post a link to your source code (e.g. on Github) instead of screenshots of part of it.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2024-07-25T17:15:37.554Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":111,"readers_count":110,"score":52.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":469111,"topic_slug":"command-groups-help","display_username":"Gavin Matthews","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":5,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38743,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)"},"post_url":"/t/command-groups-help/469111/2","custom_user_title":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3411265,"name":"","username":"mineable3","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mineable3/{size}/231504_2.png","created_at":"2024-07-25T21:41:05.339Z","cooked":"<p>I had a very similar error during my team’s first event.</p>
<p>To understand what is going on, you need to look at how the code you’re using works. Using the method <code>Commands.runOnce(Runnable, Subsystem...)</code> returns InstantCommand, not just a Command.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public static Command runOnce(Runnable action, Subsystem... requirements) {
    return new InstantCommand(action, requirements);
}
</code></pre>
<p>The Instant command will store the Runnable in its initialize() method. So when the command calls initialize(), the Runnable will execute. Then, because it’s an InstantCommand, it will immediately end.</p>
<p>The method <code>Commands.parallel(Commands...)</code> will return a ParallelCommandGroup with two InstantCommands inside. When you schedule the ParallelCommandGroup it will run the initialize() method in each InstantCommand.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">// This code is from the ParallelCommandGroup
@Override
public final void initialize() {
    for (Map.Entry&lt;Command, Boolean&gt; commandRunning : m_commands.entrySet()) {
        commandRunning.getKey().initialize();
        commandRunning.setValue(true);
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p><em>HERE</em> is when the code you want to execute will execute (sequentially). Then both commands will instantly end and the ParallelCommandGroup will also end.</p>
<p>Without understanding how <code>autonomousShoot(ms, charge)</code> and <code>autonomous(v, ms)</code> work, I am unable to recommend a solution to you. If you send a link to the code it would allow for people to make significantly more accurate recommendations.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2024-07-25T21:41:59.835Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":61,"readers_count":60,"score":12.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":469111,"topic_slug":"command-groups-help","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":66516,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Alumni"},"post_url":"/t/command-groups-help/469111/3","custom_user_title":"Alumni","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3690592,"name":"system","username":"system","avatar_template":"/uploads/default/original/4X/9/3/2/93234578e69f55873c63fc00fe2d0d85f23bce55.png","created_at":"2025-07-26T15:40:12.101Z","cooked":"<p>This topic was automatically closed 365 days after the last reply. New replies are no longer allowed.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":3,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2025-07-26T15:40:12.101Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":1,"readers_count":0,"score":0.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":469111,"topic_slug":"comma